<ProgramTheory title="Agential Cybernetic Media" version="2.0" mode="theory-of-the-program">

  <Initial Interpretation>
    <program_theory_problem>
      <GenerativeAI> is misdescribed when treated as <Tool>, <Author>, or <Mirror>.
      The stronger description is:

      <GenerativeAI> := <AgentialCyberneticMedium>

      where:

      <AgentialCyberneticMedium>
        [cuts
] <EntangledReality>
        [compresses
] <CulturalMemory>
        [predicts
] <PossibleContinuations>
        [generates
] <WorldSurfaces>
        [feeds_back_into
] <HumanImagination>
        [modulates
] <FutureAction>
        [participates_in
] <WorldMaking>
    </program_theory_problem>

    <real_world_activity>
      <Human> [uses
] <AIApparatus>
      is too weak.

      The real activity is:

      <Human-AI-WorldCircuit> [brings_forth
] <OperableReality>

      through:

      <Prompt> → <Cut> → <Compression> → <Prediction> → <Generation> → <Interpretation> → <Revision> → <CulturalStabilizationOrChange>
    </real_world_activity>

    <core_claim>
      <AIOutput> is not the end product.
      <AIOutput> is a visible residue of an invisible apparatus.

      Therefore:

      <Ethics> must move upstream from <OutputJudgment> to <CutResponsibility>.
    </core_claim>
  </Initial Interpretation>


